The paper proposes a new hyperparameter optimization method that is applicable to a wide range of problem types, including support vector machines, feed-forward neural networks, Bayesian neural networks, deep reinforcement learning, and convolutional neural networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). However, given that the paper focuses on hyperparameter optimization, which is a key aspect of machine learning, and that it proposes a new method that outperforms existing methods, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category.
